*gnome-speech-0.4.16 (13 Aug 2007)

  13 Aug 2007; Gilles Dartiguelongue <eva@gentoo.org>
  +gnome-speech-0.4.16.ebuild:
  bump to 0.4.16
  * Fix for bug 458990 - Update max speech rate in eSpeak driver 
    (Gilles Casse)

  25 Jul 2007; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> gnome-speech-0.4.11.ebuild:
  alpha stable wrt #171107

*gnome-speech-0.4.15 (24 Jul 2007)

  24 Jul 2007; Gilles Dartiguelongue <eva@gentoo.org>
  -gnome-speech-0.4.9.ebuild, -gnome-speech-0.4.10.ebuild,
  -gnome-speech-0.4.10-r1.ebuild, +gnome-speech-0.4.15.ebuild:
  bump to 0.4.15. old unstable versions cleanup. Since 0.4.11:
  * Fix for bug 454954 - Compatibility with eSpeak >=1.27 (Gilles Casse)
  * Fix for bug 443989 - when building Java platform support, add -cp option
    to work in the presence of environments where CLASSPATH might be set
  * Fix for bug 448184 - viavoicesynthesisdriver.c:718: warning: control
    reaches end of non-void function (Mario Lang)
  * Fix for bug 440169 - swift driver hardcodes voice language to en_US (Mario
    Lang)
  * Fix for bug 437867 to support festival languages without dialects.

  19 Jun 2007; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> gnome-speech-0.4.11.ebuild:
